  • 2007-08-02 14:55:35

    Re: Why flash files not view ?

    I found the problem. The solution is simple. You were right, but here are some additional details:

    1-ATutor creates courses that are numbered in order of creation. These courses make directories 1,2,3 etc. The home directory is actual one of these numbers and should be included in the path to the .swf.

    2-Windows users remember Linux doesn't like long file names. No spaces in the file names.

    3-You don't really need to use the HTML from the .swf output of your Flash app. Just import the content (.swf file) into the File Manager for the course, skip the HTML files. Then use the Graphic HTML editor Flash icon to insert the .swf, be sure and us the number [1/yourfile.swf].

    That's it. Worked for me, I hope it'll help you.
